# Release Workflow

**When you have coded, always run the full release workflow.** Do not wait to be asked. Skip only if the user explicitly says "don't release", "skip release", or similar.

When you have made any changes to this project, complete the full release workflow **after every change** unless the user explicitly says otherwise (e.g. “don’t release” or “skip release”). Do not wait to be asked.

1. **Bump version** in all of:
   - `custom_components/esphome_touch_designer/manifest.json`
   - `frontend/package.json`
   - **`README.md`** — Update the title line (e.g. `# ESPHome Touch Designer (vX.YY.ZZ)`). This is the HACS description page; HACS renders the repo README when `render_readme` is true in `hacs.json`, so the version in the first line must match the release.
   - `docs/RELEASE_NOTES.md` (add the new version heading in step 2; version number appears there too).

2. **Add a release note** for the new version in `docs/RELEASE_NOTES.md`.

3. **Run all test suites** (from repo root; all must pass before proceeding):
   ```bash
   ./scripts/run_all_tests.sh
   ```
   This runs Python tests via `pytest tests/` and frontend `npm run test`. To add a new test, add a `test_*.py` file under `tests/` or a `*.test.ts` under `frontend/src/`. If any test fails, fix before continuing. Do not release with failing tests.

4. **Rebuild the frontend** (so every release has a fresh dist; no stale assets):
   ```bash
   cd frontend && npm run build
   ```
   (This runs vitest again as part of build; that is intentional.) The build outputs to `custom_components/esphome_touch_designer/web/dist/` — stage those changes with `git add -A` in step 5.

5. **Commit and push**:
   ```bash
   git add -A && git commit -m "..." && git push origin main
   ```

6. **Create the release tag and GitHub Release** (HACS requires a GitHub Release, not just a tag):
   ```bash
   git tag vX.YY.ZZ -m "vX.YY.ZZ: brief description"
   git push origin vX.YY.ZZ
   gh release create vX.YY.ZZ --title "vX.YY.ZZ" --notes "Release notes here"
   ```
   If `gh` (GitHub CLI) is not available, create the release manually on GitHub: Releases → Create a new release → choose the tag.

7. **Direct deployment to Home Assistant** (so the integration is updated on your HA host without going through HACS). Use the **HA Vibecode Agent MCP** (user-home-assistant): for each file under `custom_components/esphome_touch_designer/` (including `web/dist/` after step 4), call **ha_write_file** with:
   - **path**: the file path relative to `/config` (e.g. `custom_components/esphome_touch_designer/__init__.py`, `custom_components/esphome_touch_designer/web/dist/index.html`).
   - **content**: the full file contents (UTF-8 text). Skip binary files if any; the frontend build outputs (JS, CSS, HTML, map) are text.
   Walk the directory recursively and write every file so that the HA host has an exact copy of the integration. Then call **ha_restart** (no arguments) via the same MCP to restart Home Assistant so the new integration code is loaded. If the Vibecode Agent MCP is not connected or the user says to skip deploy, skip step 7. Alternative: the user can deploy via SSH with `SKIP_BUILD=1 HA_HOST=... ./scripts/deploy_to_ha.sh` and then restart HA manually.

No exceptions. If you edit this project, you must do all of the above (steps 1–6; step 7 when the HA MCP is available and deploy is not skipped).
